        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Of course DD was always considered a horrific way to do damage.  It caused over argo and it was of very limited use due to the forced meditation (mana/damage ratio) a DD dealer had to go through.  DD became nothing more than “finish off the fleeing mob” type of damage.  </P><P>As bad as DD was it needed to be fixed and it was finally.  Now we have DoT, not really useful in 90% of grouping situations due to the insanely long duration the spells take to do full damage.  Add to that the inability to stack DoT damage and now DoT dealers are even more limited in usefulness.  </P><P>One part of the answer is stacking of DoT spells the other part is finding a way to increase the speed of DoT so they will not be a waste of mana in short duration fights.  </P><P><BR><center><BR>The 3yr old level 51 Necro...<img src=icon_smile_clown.gif border=0 align=middle><BR><font color=blue>Think about the word THONG.</font id=blue><BR></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
